# Demonstrates the generalized harness:
#   - SETUP=init clones the golden, build-time `zylos init` workspace, so the
#     command runs against a real post-init state (config.json, deployed skills,
#     templates) rather than a hand-written fixture.
#   - SCENARIO_CMD runs an arbitrary zylos command (not the hardcoded runtime
#     switch). `zylos runtime status` reads the runtime that init persisted.
SETUP=init
SCENARIO_CMD=zylos runtime status
EXPECT_EXIT=0
EXPECT_STDOUT=Current runtime: Claude Code (Anthropic)
EXPECT_STDERR=
